  "chapter": {
    "number": 22,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "David’s Song of Deliverance"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "And David sang this song to the LORD on the day the LORD had delivered him from the hand of all his enemies and from the hand of Saul."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "He said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“The LORD is my rock,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my fortress, and my deliverer.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My God is my rock, in whom I take refuge,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my shield, and the horn of my salvation.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "My stronghold, my refuge, and my Savior,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You save me from violence.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will call upon the LORD, who is worthy to be praised;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so shall I be saved from my enemies.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the waves of death engulfed me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the torrents of chaos overwhelmed me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The cords of Sheol entangled me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the snares of death confronted me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In my distress I called upon the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I cried out to my God.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And from His temple He heard my voice,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my cry for help reached His ears.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then the earth shook and quaked;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the foundations of the heavens",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1082
          },
          {
            "text": "trembled;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they were shaken because He burned with anger.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Smoke rose from His nostrils,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and consuming fire came from His mouth;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "glowing coals blazed forth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He parted the heavens and came down",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with dark clouds beneath His feet.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He mounted a cherub and flew;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He soared",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1083
          },
          {
            "text": "on the wings of the wind.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He made darkness a canopy around Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a gathering of water and thick clouds.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "From the brightness of His presence",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "coals of fire",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1084
          },
          {
            "text": "blazed forth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD thundered from heaven;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the voice of the Most High resounded.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He shot His arrows and scattered the foes;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He hurled lightning and routed them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The channels of the sea appeared,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the foundations of the world were exposed",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "at the rebuke of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "at the blast of the breath of His nostrils.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He reached down from on high and took hold of me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He drew me out of deep waters.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He rescued me from my powerful enemy,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from foes too mighty for me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They confronted me in my day of calamity,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the LORD was my support.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He brought me out into the open;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He rescued me because He delighted in me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD has rewarded me according to my righteousness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has repaid me according to the cleanness of my hands.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I have kept the ways of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and have not wickedly departed from my God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For all His ordinances are before me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have not disregarded His statutes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And I have been blameless before Him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and kept myself from iniquity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So the LORD has repaid me according to my righteousness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "according to my cleanness in His sight.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1085
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "To the faithful You show Yourself faithful,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the blameless You show Yourself blameless;",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "to the pure You show Yourself pure,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but to the crooked You show Yourself shrewd.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You save an afflicted people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but Your eyes are on the haughty to bring them down.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For You, O LORD, are my lamp;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD lights up my darkness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For in You I can charge an army;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with my God I can scale a wall.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As for God, His way is perfect;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the word of the LORD is flawless.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He is a shield to all",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who take refuge in Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For who is God besides the LORD?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "And who is the Rock except our God?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "God is my strong fortress",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He makes my way clear.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 34,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He makes my feet like those of a deer",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and stations me upon the heights.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 35,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He trains my hands for battle;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my arms can bend a bow of bronze.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 36,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have given me Your shield of salvation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Your gentleness exalts me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1086
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 37,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You broaden the path beneath me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that my ankles do not give way.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 38,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I pursued my enemies and destroyed them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I did not turn back until they were consumed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 39,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I devoured and crushed them so they could not rise;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they have fallen under my feet.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 40,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have armed me with strength for battle;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You have subdued my foes beneath me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 41,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have made my enemies retreat before me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I put an end to those who hated me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 42,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They looked, but there was no one to save them—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the LORD, but He did not answer.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 43,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I ground them as the dust of the earth;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I crushed and trampled them like mud in the streets.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 44,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have delivered me from the strife of my people;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You have preserved me as the head of nations;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a people I had not known shall serve me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 45,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Foreigners cower before me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when they hear me, they obey me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 46,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Foreigners lose heart",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and come trembling",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1087
          },
          {
            "text": "from their strongholds.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 47,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD lives, and blessed be my Rock!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "And may God, the Rock of my salvation, be exalted—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 48,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "the God who avenges me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and brings down nations beneath me,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 49,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who frees me from my enemies.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You exalt me above my foes;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You rescue me from violent men.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 50,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I will praise You, O LORD, among the nations;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will sing praises to Your name.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1088
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 51,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Great salvation He brings to His king.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He shows loving devotion to His anointed,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to David and his descendants forever.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
